To wrap this up, I encourage everyone to check out In The Heights in theaters or on HBO Max and just soak up the talent in this film. @ARamosofficial, @MelissaBarreraM, @lesliegrace, Corey Hawkins, @TheOlgaMerediz, Jimmy Smits, and everyone in the cast did a PHENOMENAL job👏🏽✨

The time to be yourselves is NOW! The time to show your pride and tell your stories is now!!! Sometimes, things could look like they aren’t changing for the better, but YOU can be the one to turn it all around and make it happen. Always remember that! You have POWER!!!

Fast forward 12 years later, getting to see it in theaters yesterday just brought back so much love for this show. I am so glad people all over the world will get to discover ITH! I hope it inspires people of all races, but especially my latinx brothers & sisters…we are HERE!

I have held that whole night, so close to my heart. It just showed me so many possibilities for the future. I was inspired- in life, in my career, in everything. In The Heights did that. Lin did that. Every single person who has ever had a hand in this show, did that for me.

Afterwards, Lin said that was a crazy moment for him. He was so grateful people loved him show. I told him I was so grateful he created the show!! We hugged, took lots of pictures, he signed my ITH Playbill (which I have framed in my office), and we left.

It was definitely an experience like no other! The music stopped, the crowd got quiet and there’s baby Raini and Rico rapping and singing away to the man who created it all. Lin was recording on his phone, everyone was clapping and cheering us on 🤯

When @Lin_Manuel heard that, he asked what our favorite song was, immediately we said 96,000! I told him, “I sing everyone’s parts in the car!” “I rap the rest!!”- Rico said 😂😂 And so, we started rapping and singing 96,000 for Lin right in the middle of the after party.

When @StarringRico and I finally got up to him, we couldn’t contain our excitement! I started babbling about how this show changed my life and one day I would love to play Nina in any way shape or form. Rico and I said we memorized the whole sound track too 😂

Apparently he went in through the back entrance 🤷🏽‍♀️ I finally went into the party determined to meet him and tell him how much this musical meant to me. I saw a crowd around him and patiently waited my turn….

By luck, I was able to attend the opening at the Pantages Theatre & was surprised to receive tickets to the after party. When I tell you, I waited in the entrance of that party to meet Lin, I WAITED. I was there a solid 30 mins before someone said they already saw him inside.

I did a lot of research and discovered the man responsible for this masterpiece was @Lin_Manuel.  By the time I discovered ITH it had ended it’s run on Broadway w/ the original actors, but was about to start a tour w/ a new company and its opening date would be in Los Angeles.

Growing up, I knew of theatre, but I didn’t know it could be like THAT. Music styles that I grew up listening too, story lines and life lessons that seemed to be taken right from my living room, and a stage full of people who looked like me.

I watched @intheheights movie yesterday & I cried 4 times during it. I was in a constant state of awe the entire film. From the cast, music, cinematography, direction of the story…all of it just left me feeling so happy. When I discovered this musical in 08’, it changed my life!

Everyone on and off camera worked so hard, and this movie was made with lots of love💕Thank you to the @DaytimeEmmys voters for considering our beautiful movie and good luck to everyone reaching for the same dreams! #DaytimeEmmyAwards #RekindlingChristmas
